"status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="4"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets><DescTPC fid="de"><DescField fid="ipc">G/CIA G/IGV N/CMR N/DJN N/GEN N/PLT N/WER R/NME R/US </DescField><DescField fid="ipd">NWREGULAR WSJ WSJ.com WSJ.com Site Search WSJAsia WSJEurope WSJ Japanese Online WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com WSJSunday PTC DONALD TRUMP MIKE POMPEO REX TILLERSON SECRETARY OF STATE STATE DEPARTMENT TRUMP TWEETS WHITE HOUSE CABINET SB126955385469309739639045841177902335593481 Sullivan, John Tillerson, Rex SYND CODES_REVIEWED Wires Politics and Policy </DescField><DescField fid="ipcns">OPOL </DescField></DescTPC></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">Politics</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Tillerson Tells State Department Employees to Guard Their Integrity; In farewell address, fired chief says Washington 'can be a very mean-spirited town'</Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>WASHINGTON—In a farewell <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tillerson-in-emotional-farewell-praises-u-s-diplomatic-ranks-1520973991?mod=searchresults&amp;page=1&amp;pos=20">address to State Department employees</ELink>, Secretary of State Rex Tillerson urged them to maintain their integrity and continue to hold themselves and others in government accountable.</Para><Para>"Never lose sight of your most valuable asset, the most valuable asset you possess—your personal integrity," Mr. Tillerson told a crowd of State Department officials in the department lobby.</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>"Only you can relinquish it or allow it to be compromised," he said. "Once you have done so, it is very, very hard to regain. So guard it as the most precious thing you possess."</Para><Para>Mr. Tillerson spoke only generally about the policy challenges ahead, saying that while the U.S.'s basic diplomatic strategy wouldn't change, the tactics should constantly be reviewed.</Para><Para>He never mentioned <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rex-eat-the-saladinside-the-awkward-relationship-between-rex-tillerson-and-donald-trump-1520961762?mod=searchresults&amp;page=1&amp;pos=19">President Donald Trump</ELink> or discussed the circumstances that led to <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rex-tillerson-is-out-as-secretary-of-state-donald-trump-taps-mike-pompeo-1520978116?mod=searchresults&amp;page=2&amp;pos=13">his firing in a presidential tweet</ELink>. But Mr. Tillerson's closing comments appeared to take aim at the <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/as-trump-cleans-house-who-gets-swept-out-next-1521019803?mod=searchresults&amp;page=2&amp;pos=10">bitter political climate in Washington</ELink>. He said the employees should strive to carry "one act of kindness each day toward another person."</Para><Para>"This can be a very mean-spirited town, but you don't have to choose to participate in it," he said.</Para><Para>Those remarks drew laughter and a round of applause. Mr. Tillerson then shook hands and departed the State Department for Texas. The day-to-day management of the building has already been turned over to John Sullivan, the deputy secretary of state.</Para><Para>Mr. Tillerson will officially relinquish the office at the end of the month. Mr. Trump has nominated <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pompeo-nomination-for-secretary-of-state-signals-shift-on-foreign-policy-1520963036?mod=searchresults&amp;page=1&amp;pos=17">Central Intelligence Agency Director Mike Pompeo</ELink> as the next secretary of state.</Para><Para>Write to Michael R. Gordon at <ELink type="webpage" ref="mailto:michael.gordon@wsj.com">michael.gordon@wsj.com</ELink></Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">By Michael R. Gordon </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">Copyright 2018 Dow Jones &amp; Company, Inc. All Rights Reserved. </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item><Item subtype="primary" size="0" ref="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tillerson-tells-state-department-employees-to-guard-their-integrity-1521748712" type="webpage"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

